By Abbas Bamalli Hajiya Maryam Ado-Bayero, mother of the Emirs of Kano and Bichi in Kano State, has died at the age of 80 years after a protracted illness. Alhaji Yusuf Nabahani, the Madakin Kano, confirmed the death in a statement on Saturday in Kano. He said that the deceased, who was the eldest surviving widow of Late Ado Bayero, died early Saturday in a hospital in Cairo, Egypt. Nabahani, who is also the Chairman, Kano emirate kingmakers, prayed to God to grant her mercy and abode in Aljannah Firdaus and urged the public to pray for the deceased. He said that the funeral arrangements would be announced in due course. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the deceased was a princess and elder sister to the present emir of Ilorin, Alhaji Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari. Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Late Ado Bayero's son emerges new Kano EmirBy Tukur Muntari The son of the Late Emir of Kano, Alhaji Ado Bayero has emerged the new Emir following the removal of Emir Muhammadu Sanusi 11 by Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano state. Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero, who becomes the 15th Emir of Kano was until his new appointment…March 9, 2020In "General News"Aminu Ado Bayero is new Kano EmirBy Tukur Muntari Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State has approved the appointment of Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero, as the 15th Emir of Kano, to replace Muhammadu Sunusi II. Until his new appointment, Bayero was the Emir of Bichi. Usman Alhaji, Secretary to the State Government (SSG), made the announcement…March 9, 2020In "General News"Emir of Rano dies at 74 The Emir of Rano Emirate Council in Kano State, Amb. Abubakar Tafida has died on Saturday in Kano, 